4 strong career tips for millennials from Mashable, Evernote and The Co. KL

           For millennials entering the workforce, business as usual is anything but. 
 With technology start-ups and entrepreneurs creating businesses and markets faster than ever before, digital natives flooding sometimes still-traditional positions — as well as creating their own — face a unique set of challenges. 
  See also:  3 truths about millennials that will change the way you manage them   
 With that in mind, here are four commonsense pieces of advice for millennials entering the workforce — no matter where they end up. 
     Avoid burnout .  It can be tempting to put in as much overtime as possible — answering emails at 11:00p.m., dropping by the office on the weekend — but not giving yourself any time off is sure to lead to burnout. Remember: just because you  can  work all the time doesn't mean you  should .  
    Find a mentor .  One of the best ways to navigate the workforce is to align yourself with a mentor. Finding and developing a professional relationship with someone more experienced than you can be a great resource when you're first starting out  and  a huge benefit down the line in your career when you need someone to vouch for you.  Read more...

data.message:
4 Google work secrets for boosting creativity in your company

           "How many golf balls could you fit in a school bus?" This is the kind of question Google and its big tech brethren were once known  for asking would-be employees . The reasoning behind the technique seemed intuitive. Ask people odd questions, see how original and well analyzed their thought process was, and you'll end up #hiring creative high-performers. 
 The trouble is, Google  has discovered  that the strategy doesn't actually predict people's ability to do the job. Instead, it found that it's best to ask structured questions related to what prospective employees will actually be doing — something that had been  studied for many years  by HR scholars.  Read more...  More about  Google ,  Management ,  Diversity ,  Innovation , and  Work Environment

Interested in volunteering abroad this summer? I am leading a group of students to South Africa for a 4 week volunteer program in wildlife conservation. While in South Africa students will work with nonprofit wildlife rehabilitation and rescue centers. Students will have the opportunity to assist with camera trapping, biodiversity surveys, species counts, center maintenance, animal enrichment/feeding, and education. Students will also learn about local ecology, human animal interactions, and about anti-poaching and other conservation efforts.  This is an amazing chance to experience South African culture and learn more about international conservation efforts.  This program would be great for anyone interested in conservation, education, or nonprofits. This is a very hands on learning experience. At the end of volunteering we will participate in some exciting tours. Feel free to contact me if you are interested in learning more or joining the trip! We will be traveling from the end of May through June.  You can get academic credit or internship credits through this program at the approval of your academic adviser.

data.message:
Spring 2016 Unpaid Clean Energy Policy Internship
 at NC Clean Energy Technology Center

Send resume and cover letter (single PDF) to Michael Terreri at mjterrer@ncsu.edu

Intern Skills
- attention to detail
- excellent writing and research skills
- a strong interest in learning more about renewable energy and energy efficiency policy and incentives
- ability to work independently on research assignments with minimal supervision

Type of work
- Most of the intern's time will be spent researching and summarizing utility incentives and policies for energy efficiency and renewable energy on the Database of State Incentives for Renewables and Efficiency website, which receives nearly 200,000 unique visitors every month
- A portion of the intern's work may involve other policy-related research, analysis, and writing depending on the Energy Policy Team's needs and the intern's skills and interests

Benefits to the Intern
- contributing to the nationally-recognized, high-impact DSIRE project, the most comprehensive source of public information on renewable energy and energy efficiency policies and incentives in the U.S.
- opportunity to learn in great detail about the most important drivers of renewable energy and energy efficiency in the U.S.
Mary Keilhauer

Do you like flowers? Are you looking for a part time job with reasonable hours in a fun environment with a great staff?
If so, join our sales team!
 
Fallon’s Flowers of Raleigh, located near N.C. State and Downtown Raleigh, is looking to hire Part-Time Sales Associates to work on the weekends. Our hours are 8-4 on Saturday and 9-2 on Sunday.  There will be opportunities for more hours during our busier seasons and floral holidays.

 Your Job Would Include...
- Answer incoming phone calls and enter orders into our computer system
- Provide excellent customer service both over the phone and in person
- Assist in maintaining a clean and inviting store front
- Attend to Walk-In Customers
- Restock Merchandise and flowers in the walk-in cooler
- Accurately record and communicate effectively the customer’s requests
     with your colleagues to ensure every order is successfully taken, 
      designed, and delivered as promised
 
What We are Looking For...
- Ability to use a computer and learn  our customized floral computer program
- Multitasking ability- Talking on the phone while entering orders into the
         computer
- Ability to communicate clearly with customers and colleagues
- Have interest in (or Passion for!) flowers
- Ability to provide customer service in a timely manner with a  
          professional and positive disposition
- Motivation to learn and grow in your position

We require an individual that has a great attitude and work ethic with the ability to work well individually as well as in a team environment. Highly developed people, computer and communication skills are necessary. Knowledge and/or some experience in retail, sales, customer service and/or the floral industry is helpful. 

At this time, we are ONLY looking to hire associates for the weekends. Please do not apply if this does not fit your schedule. 

To apply, please send your resume to fallonsflowers@gmail.com and/or come in to our Saint Mary’s Street location to fill out an application.

Brentwood Animal Hospital is looking for 2 veterinary assistants to start whenever they can for training. The hours we'd need someone are 2 weekdays and every other Friday from 4pm until between 8-9pm and every other Saturday, Sunday, and holiday with varying hours. 

The position requires no previous experience and is paid; one will be required to lift objects (generally dogs) weighing up to 50 lbs. Many of the hours are worked as a vet tech assisting in exams, vaccinations, nail trims, etc; the rest will be basic janitorial work for the hospital along with caring for the animals that stay the night. We're a small staff so picking up extra hours is something that can be easily done, these extra hours will likely be spent as a vet tech, but sometimes can have one assisting in surgeries. 

Brentwood Animal Hospital is a cats and dogs practice in North Raleigh with two experienced doctors (Dr. Steve Neuenschwander and Dr. Amanda Hild). We're open every day except Sunday but ask that people interested stop by during the week between 1pm and 3pm (if that doesn't fit your schedule feel free to come by and pick up an application whenever you can).

Hello,

I am reaching out to you from New Mind Education, an organization affiliated with NCSU that works with incoming international students.  Currently, all of our students are from China, and many spend their first year at NCSU enrolled in the university's Intensive English Program (IEP).  For more information on our program, please visit our website:  http://www.newmind.org

We are currently looking for a Chinese-speaking intern who would be interested in gaining AP Calculus teaching experience, in collaboration with the North Carolina School of Science and Math (NCSSM). Our intern would be working closely with NCSSM instructors, and our New Mind staff, to be an on-campus support for our students as they work through the web-based curriculum.

The ideal candidate is fluent in Mandarin, and highly proficient in the content of AP Calculus AB.  The summer responsibilities of this position would entail assisting NCSSM instructors in the proper translation of key terminology from English to Mandarin and course preparation.  Job responsibilities during the fall and spring semesters would consist of two weekly meetings with a group of students, one being a class session and the other a tutorial session, and offering continuous support remotely. Does anyone know of a financial analyst job (preferably in stocks or investment) which don't require a degree in finance or business?  I have a chemistry degree, but I don't want to pay to take the 43 more credit hours to finish a degree in finance.  I have taken ACC 200 (Manageral Accounting), ACC 210 (Financial Accounting), BUS 225 (Intro to Personal Finance), BUS 320 (Intro to Portfolio Management), BUS 350 (Business Statistics), BUS 420 (Corporate Finance), BUS 422 (Portfolio Management), BUS 425 (Advanced Personal Finance), and BUS 495 (Intro to Business Analytics).  I also worked as a freelance stock writer for four years.
if you have any desire to relocate, I know of some in Atlanta

Elizabeth Eichen: Can you message me the job description.  I preferably want something near Raleigh/Apex/Cary area.  But as a last option, I may have to relocate.  Thanks.  I'm on LinkedIn too, but it is very hard to find a finance job without a finance degree or experience.
I'm physically disabled, so chemistry jobs which I can do with just a bachelors degree is not easy to find either.  Finance is my hobby.  I been watching the stock market since 7th grade.

I would look into becoming a consultant. But you would need references for that. It would help if you could find someone that would allow you to help them, and then work off of that. It's worth trying to network into a position like that, LinkedIn is an especially good tool for that. In a year or so I will be looking for someone to help with some of my investments. I'm sorry I can't be of any help really now.
Stephen Lichtenwalner: So you could become my client in a year. :D  And no worry, I need to build my client base.  Wonder what the legal requirements are to charge people for consulting.

Most likely :D I need at least some consulting, especially being fresh into investing. I've devoted almost all of my research time into investing but it's always good to have someone who already knows!
Try networking on LinkedIn! It's seriously great. You can add me if you want, I've spent some time making sure mine is solid.

I currently work for a major banking institution and I graduated from NCSU with my bachelor's in Business Admin - Finance concentration. It ultimately depends on what you want to do... if you want to be an analyst, and by that I mean involved in market research, forecasting, and number crunching markets, then you definitely need to sign on with a firm that caters to that specifically. In the finance field analysts tend to make a lot less than what you originally think they should (40-60K).  If your interest is in trading on the market and fully maximizing the benefits of the finance field then you should start at a bank. Banks hire teller's all the time and with the way turnover is people are always moving in to banker's chairs. To get to trade on wall street most people start as teller's at banks (if they dont have degrees) and work their way up within 5 years to becoming licensed bankers. The only way to trade is by getting licensed and the only way to get licensed is by corporate sponsorship... so if your goal is to work in finance and make an amazing living off of it then your goal should be to become a licensed trader and the easiest way to do that when your background isn't in the field is to start working at a bank.

How do you go about finding positions on campus particularly in the social sciences that would involve data management using programs such as Stata and SAS?  Health research would be perfect.  I am in a hard science major with two years of hard science research experience and am doing social science research this summer using Stata and would like to continue that.  Any ideas?

jobs.ncsu.edu is honestly your best bet. You'll find that quite a lot of research assistant positions are needed. Either that, or, you actually have a better shot just going to your professors, saying, I'm here, this is my experience, and I want to work, and you'll find often there's work to do!
Thanks!  I always see stuff for departments like horticulture and entomology but rarely social sciences on there..

Admittedly, less research assistance is needed for the social sciences, but if you can show you can run good multivariate regressions etc. using statistical software, I'm sure a couple of professors will have at least little bits of work for you to do! I'm in the School of Public and International Affairs and fairly inundated!

I know so little about that side of campus simply because I was in Biochemistry for so long but I have been using Stata all summer working with the Add Health data.  I may not have the most experience but know a bit and willing to learn more because I really like it, a lot more than bench science actually!

I'd also email professors who are doing research you're interested in to see if they need anyone. It also couldn't hurt to get familiar with other stats software (specifically R, which is a giant pain but it's super useful).

Waitress, Hostess, Nanny, Store, Restaurant, etc. I already have a pretty cool (unpaid) internship. I just need a job to help me pay my rent.

With retail and restaurant jobs they pretty much hire right away.  The best thing is to go in between 2 and 4pm and ask about job openings.  Most restaurants won't hire you as a server or bartender if you don't have experience, but you can start as a hostess.  The more expensive the restaurant, the better the pay and tips.  Most retail is around minimum wage, and upscale restaurants pay better.  I worked both in high school and college, and I got up to $11/hr hosting versus $8/hr retail.  Just look cute and be friendly, they hire for personality.

New Mind Education is a dynamic Raleigh-based company focused on inspiring and cultivating global talent. We are seeking motivated and responsible interns to mentor and support Chinese exchange students who are preparing to enroll full-time at NC State. Most of the students will be in IEP (Intensive English Program), though we will have a small group that will be directly admitted and taking freshman courses at NC State.     

Specifically, we need interns to help with our extended orientation July 23-August 14. 

The internship will begin with a training session on Thursday, July 23rd. On July 25, interns and New Mind staff will also attend a Shelton Leadership training session at 10am. Both sessions will be held on Main Campus. 

On July 26-31, interns will be working full time and staying with the students and staff in Turlington Hall, Main Campus. Rooms and meals will be covered for this first week! It will be a fun, but FULL, busy week! Each intern will be assigned to one staff member and a group of 8-12 New Mind students, which you will work with for the week. Shelton Leadership classes and activities will be held on Main Campus.   

On July 31st we will be moving the students from Turlington to Wolf Ridge, Centennial Campus. Interns will need their own places to stay from that point on. During these next two weeks (July 31-August 14) New Mind staff will teach workshops, and interns will assist events such as a campus scavenger hunt. Interns will also help with group activities, plan and run panels or create informational presentations (on topics such as American culture social media, academic advice, transportation), but the workload/hours will not be as intense as the first week.

On August 11th we will be moving the students from Wolf Ridge to Alexander Hall or University Towers. Interns will assist students and staff as needed.  

Finally, on August 14th will be our mixer event: a BBQ in Pullen Park. Interns will help plan, coordinate and execute this event, and enjoy it after all their hard work!

Some compensation is available, and it will be rewarding to connect with bright international students and teach them about American culture! New Mind staff will also be happy to provide recommendation letters or serve as references. 

Duties include: 

• Translating directions of staff members to Chinese students
• Providing assistance to staff as needed
• Mentoring New Mind students
• Help plan and execute student activities
• Create and present panels or presentations as needed

Requirements: 

• NC State student 
• Proficiency in Mandarin preferred
• Enthusiasm!
• Organized, dependable, adaptable
• Comfortable with international students
• Comfortable in large groups

Please send your resume to eholloway@newmindedu.com if interested!
Aakash Sarav

Learn To Become A Certified Pharmacy Technician Today!

Greetings All,

Faith Drake is  currently recruiting individuals that are interested in becoming a certified pharmacy technician. This summer I will be teaching a course on behalf of Gericare Education and Training Inc. located in Durham, NC. Classes will be held 3 days a week on Monday, Wednesday, and Friday; however, this could change depending on the amount of participation. They will be held in the mornings from 10:30AM-12:30PM and/or 7:00PM-9:00PM, but my schedule is flexible for those that need accommodations. Classes will begin Wednesday June 17, 2015 and will last for 8 weeks.

This course is open to everyone, with only a high school diploma or equivalent educational diploma required. If you lack or want to improve on pharmacy experience, this program is ideal for you. With your willpower, I will provide you with the confidence and experience to be an asset to any pharmaceutical industry. This is a valuable opportunity of growth this summer for recent high school graduates as well as current college students. Below is the link for the book I will be teaching from. The book is included in the cost of this class.

http://www.pearsonhighered.com/educator/product/Pharmacy-Technician-The-Foundations-and-Practice/9780132897594.page

There is a fee of $1382 for this course. Payment options include:

1) Pay the full cost up front
2) Pay $500 upfront, and make weekly/biweekly installments while taking the course
3) Apply for the in-house loan program, and make a 25% down payment

Below is the link for information on the loan.
http://eba-na.com/In-House-Consumer-Financing-Program.php

I can direct you to a Gericare Education and Training Inc. representative if you have questions or need more details about the loan process.

In contrast to competitors, this program is only 8 weeks. Other local programs take at least 12 months to complete. The price is also significantly lower through Gericare.

I'll leave you with this thought:
"Give a man a fish, feed him for a day; teach a man to fish and you feed him for a lifetime".

If you are interested message me on Facebook or email me at fndrake@ncsu.edu

data.message:
New Mind Education is a dynamic Raleigh-based company focused on inspiring and cultivating global talent. We are seeking motivated and responsible NC State students to mentor and support Chinese exchange students who are preparing to enroll full-time at NC State. Most of the students will be in IEP (Intensive English Program), though we will have a small group that will be directly admitted and taking freshman courses at NC State.     

The New Mind Program starts July 24th. I realize that is an atypical time and many of you will not be able to start that early. If you ARE available to help during that time, please let me know! Special compensation is available for helping with Orientation activities and aiding the staff. 

Otherwise, the dates are August 14-December 16th. It is unpaid and part-time but some compensation, recommendations or other services are available. 

All interns are expected to: 
• Attend a weekly intern meeting
• Help create posters/decorations for events
• Help plan, execute and attend most of the New Mind student life events
• Support the New Mind Global Learning Community (GLC) and advising efforts
• Propose new ideas, events, or campus/community connections
• Engage with New Mind students and help them integrate into campus  
• Respond to all emails/WeChat messages in a timely manner
• Mentor 5-10 New Mind Students by checking in at least 2x a week
• Perform other duties as assigned 

Specific Intern positions include: Media, Campus Liaison, and Service Learning. Inquire for the responsibilities of each one. 

Qualifications:
Required
• Current NC State student
• Familiar with Google Docs, Drive, Facebook/Social Media
• Passionate about helping fellow students
• Interest in promoting cultural exchange
• Proactive in collaborating and communicating with peers
• Wish to develop leadership skills
• Responsible, organized, and friendly
Preferred
• Interest in East Asian culture 
• Conversational level OR interest in Mandarin language 
• Experience in working with international students 

Please forward your questions, resume and cover letter to: studentlifecoordinatornm@gmail.com

Great job opportunity at a startup here in Raleigh!  If you're interested please send your resume to Chas@crateclique.com today! 

About CrateClique:

CrateClique is an online subscription group that manages different subscription businesses. We are currently seeking a co-founder to help manage our first subscription business, BubbleBatch.  BubbleBatch is a subscription service that delivers customized, sustainable bath, spa and relaxation products on a monthly basis. If you are design-oriented, self-motivated, and want to get in on the ground floor of an exciting startup, contact us today. 

Job Description:

BubbleBatch is seeking a co-founder to help manage the company. Since this is an early-stage startup, the job duties will vary. First and foremost, you will be a partner to the company, with a vested interest in helping expand the product line and grow business. Technical proficiency is preferable, Social Media experience is mandatory. You will be expected to manage the companies social media, keep track of orders and shipping, assist with company branding, and prepare weekly statements on the progress of the business. 

Compensation will vary with experience, but you will directly benefit from every sale we have. As a co-founder, you will receive a portion of the companies profits. 

Desired Qualifications: 

Have a college degree, or be in the process of pursuing one. Majors are unimportant as long as you are motivated, hardworking, and creative. Experience in any of the following is preferred: Sales, Marketing, Social Media, Design. The most important requirement is that you are a self-motivated go getter who wants to be part of an awesome startup. Send your resume to: Chas@crateclique.com today.
is this a full time job?

I would say it is more like a never ending job.  As a co-founder or founder, you work as much as necessary to keep the company afloat.  But maybe it is different if the company has a CEO, where the CEO can manage the company.
Since this job essentially requires running a business, a full-time effort is expected.  However, we are flexible on time commitment as long as the job is getting done!

Music Industry Opportunity! 

HOPE TREE ENTERTAINMENT seeks industry intern
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

Consider an internship with Hope Tree Entertainment, LLC (HTE) and become an integral part of one of the leading independent forces in music content today.

With a broad roster of independent artists, HTE is home to a collection of some of the nation’s most inspiring projects. Providing consumers a broad array of quality music depends on maintaining an inspired and entrepreneurial environment full of talented and diligent individuals.
HTE prides itself on promoting and nurturing individual achievement while working to achieve company goals.
HTE strives to create a workplace that enables both interns and the company to reach their highest potential. 
Given HTE's wide-ranging services, individuals may gain a deeper understanding of social marketing, video and audio production, booking, publishing, and many more essential verticals of the independent market. 

An internship with Hope Tree Entertainment provides students with the opportunity to obtain real world experience at one of the top independent label service music companies in the industry. Our internships provide on-the-job training by allowing interns to shadow industry professionals in a variety of industry tasks. Every intern is assigned a special project that will both assist them in increasing their understanding of how label services departments operate, and aid those departments in addressing a business need. Hope Tree Entertainment values its interns, as such we have developed an educational program including first hand interaction with our vast network of industry professionals to ensure a mutually rewarding experience.

Individuals with an intern interest must possess adequate grammar skills, ambition, work ethic and the ability to receive college credit for their internship. 

Please forward interest to hopetreeentertainment@gmail.com

data.message: Hey Y'all! I have a neighbor that is looking for before school care and after school care for her 5th grader. She lives in Prestonwood (Cary,NC) so its not to far away from campus. She is looking for someone available to care for her daughter ASAP. The ideal match would be available to come to her house at least 2-3 times a week at 7:30am and take her child to school at 9am. Then hopefully the same person also help at least 2-3 times a week from when she gets picked up at school at 3:45-5pm. She is in Year-round school so there are a few days where you need to be available for the occasional early release at 1:15 versus the usually 3:45 time. She is looking for a fun and responsible babysitter that can get to know her and her child over the next few months and possibly summer. Hey guys! I was chosen to be a designer in a fashion show coming up called "Couture for a Cause." This is a fundraising event to benefit Activate Good, which is a group that pairs with other local, non-profits and volunteers to promote support and business for all. This event brings in over 500 guests and is quite a show! We (local designers) are competing for a chance to win a prize in Couture Ready-to-Wear categories, but it means so much more to me than that. I am not majoring in design or textiles (I wish I had-hindsight is 20/20) but I am a Business Marketing major who just happens to have a serious love for fashion and design (it's what I want to do for a career), and I'm already shocked and honored that I was even selected to contribute compete as a designer! At the end of the runway show, the pieces we have created are auctioned off and the proceeds go towards the cause each designer has been paired with. I have been paired with AniMall, a rescue organization that finds homes for all types of homeless animals-not just cats and dogs! They are located at Cary Towne Center and I recently (before I even knew about this design competition) adopted my two furry little soul mates (that's exactly what they are to me:)) from AniMall, so it really does mean so much to me to be participating in so many ways!

Point of my post (so sorry this was so extensive): I am in need of someone to actually sew my ensembles for me. I have to put together two full outfits and can acquire all of the materials necessary, but the actual process of assembling is a bit lost on me! My mom and aunt can sew very well, but they are in Charlotte so they can only help so much! This would be a great learning opportunity and a substantial and credible event that you can add your resume for experience, volunteerism, and involvement! Not to mention, this is for a great cause-not for me, but for all of the organizations that are participating and involved...they really are all so unique and their stories and missions are touching.

Please let me know if you or ANYONE you know would be willing to help me in any way. I promise we will make it fun, I can bake yummy snacks and treats for fuel and compensation! Both of these ensembles must be made by November 1, but the fashion show is not until November 15. And you do not need to be at either event if you don't want to come. I know this is a very short frame of time, but I just found this out less than a week ago and have been sorting out the logistics of it since! I can email you the sketches of the outfits also and the descriptions of them, as well.

Thank you so much for taking the time to read this, I'm sorry it was so much info!

In case you are interested, here is the website for the event: http://activategood.org/coutureforacause/
And for Animall: http://www.animall.org/
And the FB page for Couture for a Cause: https://www.facebook.com/activategood.coutureforacause/photos_stream

data.message: I'm wondering if anyone here has used tutor.com as a means to get paid for tutoring. Is it legit? How much did you make hourly? Etc etc.
Good question. I received an email to that effect and I was already wondering if I should consider it or not.  Any ideas guys?
I would check out wyzant.com! They are a tutoring service.
And you set your own rates and have to take short quizzes on the subjects in order to be considered qualified to tutor in said subjects.
I'm interested in tutor.com since they are specifically looking for comp sci tutors.
Okay. Well I know that wyzant is legit and that students are looking for a variety of tutors so if you don't want to risk joining something that's potentially illegitimate, you can go there.

I haven't personally used tutor.com for tutoring but I did start their become a tutor process a while back and for each subject there's like a 1-3 hour test you have to take and you can't stop in the middle of the test without having to start over again. Not really a deal breaker, but a huge inconvenience and it was enough to deter me from continuing after I did the first math one for algebra. Take that with a grain of salt though, but I haven't heard back from them as to whether or not I "passed" and that was about 7 months ago.
I think everyone with comp sci intent got that email, and honestly its legitimacy is not very promising.
A lot of online tutoring sites require undergraduate if not graduate degrees. Not sure if tutor.com is one of them, but make sure you're qualified before spending a few hours taking exams! :)
https://www.facebook.com/triangletutorconnection

Busy veterinary practice located in the Wendell area seeking an experienced Veterinary Assistant and Front Receptionist.  Must be able to thrive in a fast-paced environment, be a team player, have a positive attitude, and feel comfortable with client communications. 

We are looking for highly motivated individuals capable of multi-tasking to join our state-of-the-art facility.  Our facility includes a surgery suite, a radiology suite, a dental station, a lab for specimen analysis, and much more.  This is an excellent, challenging environment in which you can expand both your knowledge and skills. 

Front Receptionist

-Must feel comfortable answering phones, scheduling appointments, prepping and verifying patient charts, and experience with Avimark Software is preferred, but not required.
-We expect you to be comfortable educating clients about vaccines, medications, flea/tick preventatives, and heartworm preventatives.
-Maintaining a friendly, professional manner when dealing with clients is imperative. 

Veterinary Assistant

-Be skilled in animal restraint, sample collection and analysis, client education, and monitoring patients under anesthesia. 
-May also be required to assist in kennel.  Kennel duties include: walking, feeding, and medicating boarders, bathing patients, cleaning runs and cages, cleaning and sterilizing surgical instruments, and helping out wherever needed.
-Be knowledgeable of vaccine protocols, prescription medications, all heartworm and flea/tick preventatives, and must feel comfortable making recommendations to clients. 
 
Experience is preferred but not necessary.  Salary will be correlated with experience.  Will be flexible with student schedules (some evenings until 7 pm and weekends, too).  We are located approximately 21 miles (25 minutes) away from campus.  Please fax resume to Kim Murray at 919-365-0704 or call at 919-365-9001.  You can also email your resume to kmurray915@hotmail.com.

data.message:
Hello everyone,
Gourmet Factory on Western boulevard (right across from cook out) is looking to a hire a new server and new delivery driver! 
Server: duties include answering phones, taking orders (delivery and dine in), serving tables (of course), and cleaning the dining area as well as various other tasks.  Looking for people that are either experienced servers or good at multitasking and keeping cool when it gets really busy. Servers should be sociable and are encouraged to get to know customers since most of our dine in business is with regular customers.
Driver: duties include assisting kitchen staff with preparation and dishes when they aren't out on deliveries, as well as of course taking deliveries. We are looking for someone that works well with others (you'll be spending most of your time back in the kitchen and it can be pretty hectic), a quick learner, and is good at following directions.
Hours for both positions are flexible. The application process is simple, and we are looking to hire someone immediately for both positions. If you have questions, you can message me or comment.
Application process: call the restaurant, tell them you are interested in the position, and ask to be able to come in and have an interview with Thomas (manager).  Best times to come in are between 2-4 ( business is slowest in these hours). Bring a copy of your resume with you to the interview. And, if you get the position you'll get a call from the manager soon after, or if you make a really good impression he may start talking hours with you before you leave the interview.
Choua Lee
What is the pay?

$7.25 plus tips, unless you're making more than 7.25 an hr in tips, in which case the hourly pay will drop to 2.50

No, if you make a $7.25 tip then your pay will drop down to $2.50 (as it was explained to me).

data.message:
Research Scientist (KC)
Research Triangle, NC
12 Month Contract
Rate: $24.00/hr w2

Job Description:
The Research Scientist will work together with a Team Leader and four Research Scientists in the Screening Team of Global Insecticide Biology Research. The candidate will conduct experiments based on established protocols and conduct biological assays in the laboratory to identify Client chemistry for efficacy on crop pest targets; weigh, formulate, and apply experimental and commercial compounds to pest targets and crops; and assess insect behavior, susceptibility, and crop injury impact.

Qualifications
BS or MS in an area of whole organism biology with course work in entomology, pest management or crop management. Must have the ability to work as a member of a multidisciplinary research team. Candidate will work in laboratory and greenhouse environments, and be willing and able to handle insects and chemicals of unknown toxicity. Daily work will include routine tasks including preparing plants, insects and chemical solutions, and evaluating the effectiveness of potential insecticides. Computer skills required: MS-Word and Excel. Weekend work will be required two weekends/month. A background in entomology or experience in crop protection, and agricultural insecticide applications is highly desirable. Previous experience working with an agricultural products company would be a plus.

Send me your resume if interested
Ahmed Farawi

data.name: WKNC Summer Training Class for New DJs/Staff
data.caption: WKNC Summer Training Class for New DJs/Staff
data.description:
Want to get radio experience as a student at NC State? Want to spin the best music you can hear on the radio? Want to meet the best friends anyone could ever ask for?!

WKNC is looking for full-time students from NC State to become the next generation of DJs and staff members of the station. If you're interested in learning how you can become involved or a little more about all of the cool stuff that we do, this is your chance. 

Here's what you need to do:

1. Attend our interest meeting, held on Tuesday 05/20 from 6-7 in Witherspoon 356
2. All interest inquiries (the application you will receive at the interest meeting) will be due that Friday, 05/23 before 5 pm
3. Attend the training classes: 05/27-06/24: Tuesdays from 6-7 pm 
4. Attend the co-curricular in-studio training with an assigned DJ to shadow once per week for one hour at a time convenient for you.

*Interest meeting attendance is required in order to apply for training classes.

*meetings and classes will be held in Witherspoon 356 from 6-7

WKNC puts on concerts, plays amazing music, and has a staff of ~120 students and community members. It's a ton of fun, and we'd love for some new faces!

data.message: Is there a way to get involved with the station besides DJing?
Of course! Attend out interest session in Witherspoon on May 20th (more info on the event) if you can and you can meet everyone and show you around. You don't have to take the DJ class.
